        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 2 at 7:16PM MDT until July 2 at 7:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Fourchette, or
33 miles southeast of Zortman, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Fourchette, Devils Creek Rec Area, U L Bend Rec Area, Crooked Creek
Rec Area, Phillips, Sun Prairie, and Fred Robinson Bridge.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
